nistrators     Help     Sandbox     Recent Changes                          in: Gobstones players, Males, Welsh individuals, Wizards            Grugwyn Rufford              View source                         History                         Talk (0)                                   Grugwyn Rufford   Biographical information  Born 1981 or earlier[1]   Nationality Welsh[2]    Physical information  Species Human[2]   Gender Male[2]    Affiliation  Loyalty National Welsh Gobstones Team[2]   [Source]  Grugwyn Rufford (fl. 1998) was a Welsh wizard who was a member of the National Welsh Gobstones Team.[2]  Contents  1 Biography 2 Etymology 3 Appearances 4 Notes and references   Biography In 1998, Rufford complained to the Daily Prophet because they did not cover the Welsh victory over Hungary. On 31 July that year, the editor replied to him via an editorial saying that people found that Gobstones were "deeply boring".[2]  Etymology It is possible that this name 'Grugwyn' comes from Welsh grug gwyn "white heather".  Appearances Daily Prophet Newsletters (First mentioned) Notes and references   ↑ As a member of a National Gobstones Team, he was likely over 17.  ↑ 2.0 2.1 2.2 2.3 2.4 2.5 Daily Prophet Newsletters: 31 July, 1998, Page 3              Categories         Categories:   Gobstones players    Males    Welsh individuals    Wizards           *Disclosure: Some of the links above are affiliate links, meaning, at no additional cost to you, Fandom will earn a commission if you click through and make a purchase. Community content is available under CC-BY-SA unless otherwise noted.             Advertisement     Fan Feed        More Harry Potter Wiki     1 Sirius Black     2 Hufflepuff     3 Ravenclaw                           Explore Wikis            Universal Conquest Wiki        Let's Go Luna! Wiki        Club 57 Wiki                              Explore properties          Fandom               Cortex RPG               Muthead               Futhead               Fanatical